Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 12:12:36 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 12/15] Map xhigh natively on the Anthropic Messages wire

Pass xhigh through as its own adaptive effort instead of collapsing it to
max: pi's model data has native xhigh as a distinct level between high
and max on Opus 4.7/4.8, Sonnet 5, and Fable 5. Offer xhigh on exactly
those catalog entries, resolve a requested xhigh to an offered max on
models without it (mirroring the existing max-to-xhigh legacy downgrade),
and document that custom Messages entries for older Claude models should
use max, which every adaptive model accepts.
